              Nothing that affected conversions. Nothing that justified <strong class="text-[#A855F7]">$126 extra</strong> or
              <strong class="text-[#A855F7]">5 days of waiting</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-[#A855F7] p-6 my-6">
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">WHEN B12'S HUMAN REVIEW IS WORTH IT</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">
              A lawyer needed absolute professionalism and didn't care about cost. He used B12.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              The designer refined his copy to sound more authoritative. tightened headings, improved whitespace hierarchy.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Result:</strong> 12 clients at $5,000 each = <span class="text-[#A855F7]">$60,000 revenue</span>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              The extra $180/year didn't matter. The polished look signaled competence worth paying for.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-violet-100 border-l-[4px] border-violet-500 p-6 my-6">
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">THE LESSON</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-800">
              B12's human review helps if you're in a field where <strong class="text-gray-900">polish justifies premium pricing</strong>
